参数3_文本: FM住Hall如果俾人欺凌，遇上不公義事件唔使啞忍架。為大家簡介香港嘅法律援助 (Access to the law is Fundamental human right)Duty Lawyer Service （值日生）-The free legal advise scheme Offers preliminary legal advise No means test or charges Applicants must approach a local social welfare organization to make an appointment (NO walk-in)20-30 mins general legal advise on each case, BUT NO follow-up advise or formal legal representation through the scheme如果欺凌事件涉及民事成份，都唔怕冇錢打官司架(刑事案件直接報警就得—>律政司)The Legal Aid Department -Ordinary Legal Aid schemeFor civil cases including but not limited to:Nuisance 妨擾Negligence 疏忽EXCEPTDefamation 誹謗Claims ($75,000 or less) in the Small Claims Tribunal Need to pass BOTH means and merit test(Financial resources of $0-$52500 NO need to pay any contribution)Means test: $0-420400Merit test: Reasonable grounds(Impoliteness is not a reasonable ground)**Director‘s first chargeCosts incurred in providing legal aid in that case must be deducted from damages recovered through the action （補差額)

According to the HKU Intellectual Property Rights Policy (https://tl.hku.hk/to-protect-educational-materials/ and http://www.rss.hku.hk/contracts/ipr), HKU shall own all intellectual property rights in educational materials generated by staff in the course of their employment with the University.  Educational materials include all forms of materials for teaching & learning and assessment purposes.  Under no circumstances shall these materials be reproduced, distributed or sold without the consent of HKU or the teachers.  We would like to reiterate that intellectual property infringement is also taken very seriously by the University as a matter of academic integrity and honesty.  The School has zero tolerance towards any forms of intellectual property infringement.  In all fairness and with due respect to our teachers who have contributed intellectual inputs to those teaching materials, the University may seek redress for such infringement by taking legal action against the infringers and/or to report the offences to the appropriate regulatory authorities/professional bodies (including the HKSAR Customs and Excise Department) and HKU Disciplinary Committee via the Faculty for follow-up/enforcement/disciplinary actions. As well-educated persons, you are expected to follow the principle that knowledge is to be shared for academic exchange and development rather than treated as commodities for unauthorised monetary gain.  We appeal to you for your full cooperation in helping to safeguard the intellectual property rights of the University.  Regards, Chia-Chin LinProfessor and Head

参数1_文本: 唔好再講「地鐵」，係蝗語黎
参数5_文本: 就奇！依一兩年係連登見到越黎越多蝗語特警亂鳩咁黎，將一啲香港沿用多年、又或者係一啲書面語、縮寫批鬥成蝗語既風氣大行其道，以下係一啲例子：沿用多年奶奶，例句「我奶奶好難頂，我要返外家」，依個詞語只要你有睇下cctvb 80-90年代初既出品既電視劇就實有聽過。一會兒，例句「小明午睡了一會兒，便繼續溫習」。依個詞語歸類落書面語系列都得。可能因為兒化音啦，連登班蝗語特警一見到個兒字就大力批鬥。我唔排除「一會兒」依個詞語一開頭真係由北方傳落黎香港，但我就1990年香港出世，讀教會營辦、非左派學校，幼稚園、小學學中文已經教緊「一會兒」依個詞語。歡迎70後、80後出黎指正。書面語支付，依個字明明只係一個普通既書面語，但可能因為鄰國有樣野叫「支付寶」啦，開始連依個詞語都被批鬥為蝗語綜藝，我係隔離post見到，佢被批為蝗語既理據我就唔係好睇到。https://lih.kg/2999770縮寫團綜由上面個post延伸以黎。依個驟眼睇可能似蝗語，但其實只係一個中性既縮寫。縮寫既原因，一個字：懶。但其實香港係港英時期已經有大量依啲縮寫詞語，例如：超市(超級市場)、腿通(火腿通粉)、腿旦治(火腿雞蛋三文治)、紅隧(紅磡海底隧道)、皇家馬德里(皇馬)、公廁(公共廁所)、美國(美利堅眾合國)你可以屌依班用縮寫既人懶、縮寫到外人難以理解，但唔應該將依啲縮寫字批鬥為蝗語。你可以屌係社交媒體用書面語既打文既人矯揉造作、懶感性懶文青(文青都已經係縮寫，你有冇用過？），但唔好將自己日常少用既書面語批鬥為蝗語我地要小心既係一啲共產黨獨有/地方色彩濃厚既詞語，例如接地氣、鑽空子、一步到位、吃貨、小區、公車依啲字眼，而唔係自我閹割其他絕大部份華語圈都會共用既字詞。語言係思想既載體，我地小心蝗語入侵既同時，都唔好自我閹割埋其他用黎正確表達自己思想既文字，最後受惠既可能係對家。

Discuss the steps involved.Answer: The process of developing and maintaining a strategic fit between the organization's goals and capabilities and its marketing opportunities is called strategic planning. At the outset, beginning at the corporate level, each company must define its overall purpose and mission. What is our business? Who is the customer? What do our customers value? Answers to these questions are crucial in writing a clear mission statement. Mission statements need to be carefully defined in terms of customer needs. Missions should be realistic, motivating, and fit the market environment. Missions then lead to setting business and marketing objectives/goals in the planning process. This is followed by decisions regarding what portfolio of businesses and products is best for the company and how much support to give each one. Next, each business and product develops detailed marketing and other functional strategies. In this step, plans are drawn at the business unit, product, and market levels in support of company wide plans.Diff: 2 Page Ref: 38AACSB: CommunicationSkill: ConceptObjective: 2-1
